summary:
"Lobbying is at the core of democracy"
(https://www.parliament.uk/about/living-heritage/building/palace/architecture/palace-s-interiors/central-lobby)

Experienced lobbyist and public affairs professional representing PostNL (former TNT Post) from 2005 to 2020 in Brussels. Nowadays Jan Bart shares his experience and network with other organizations as consultant for public affairs and strategy from his own firm EUconsult in Rotterdam or through his associated partnership with Dr2 Consultants in Brussels.

With a civil engineering and business administration background, Jan Bart started his career in 1978 as design and site engineer at Shell. Prior to joining TNT Post he worked in marketing and regional management at Philips Electronics and as consultant in two business development firms.

Jan Bart, a Dutch national, has a wealth of international experience. He was posted for work in Asia, Central Europe and the Middle East; and he lived in the UK and South Africa to complete his education. 

"Defining a clear message and aligning parties behind it is my strength. In national lobbying, stakeholder alliances are useful; in EU lobbying they are a must."
